{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":6},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5},"À propos d’une inscription funéraire paléochrétienne de Mégara Hyblaea","","2011","\u003Cspan>Henry Tréziny, « À propos d’une inscription funéraire paléochrétienne de Mégara Hyblaea », \u003Ci>Provence Historique. Hommages à Jean Guyon\u003C/i> 61, n\u003Csup>o\u003C/sup> 243‑244 (2011): 127‑34\u003C/span>",[7,115],{"file":8,"uri":8,"title":9,"status":10,"editionAuthor":12,"type":13,"objectType":17,"material":21,"condition":3,"layoutDesc":25,"handNote":32,"date":53,"places":59,"geo":68,"provenance":61,"provenanceGeo":72,"country":73,"region":74,"settlement":61,"repository":75,"textLang":79,"tmNumber":3,"facsimile":83,"letterHeights":90,"publications":91,"zotero":94,"keywords":97,"html":108,"bibl":109},"ISic004390","Fragmentary early Christian funerary inscription",{"_":11},"edited",null,{"_":14,"ana":15,"ref":16},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",{"_":18,"ana":19,"ref":20},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html",{"_":22,"ana":23,"ref":24},"marble\n                                    ","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"layout":26},{"p":27,"rs":28,"damage":3},"Remains of three lines of Greek letters, with small space to the margin at top, and vacat to the right and a roughly consistent right margin, suggesting line ends are preserved. The letters on the fourth fragment are smaller, and preserve vacat to the left suggesting line beginning. A further line is partially preserved on the fourth fragment.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":33,"dimensions":34},"The letters are fairly regularly cut, with almost no serifs/terminations to the strokes, excpt for the slight extension of the apex of alpha and delta. Alpha has broken bar; omicron is slightly ovoid and full size; pi has equal length verticals; epsilon is lunate; phi is rhomboid.",[35,41,45,49],{"type":36,"l":37,"from":38,"to":38,"h":39,"unit":40},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","12","mm",{"type":36,"l":42,"from":43,"to":43,"h":44,"unit":40},"Line 2","line2","12-14",{"type":46,"l":47,"from":38,"to":43,"h":48,"unit":40},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","2",{"type":46,"l":50,"from":43,"to":51,"h":52,"unit":40},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","line3","1-2",{"_":54,"notBefore":55,"notAfter":56,"evidence":57,"precision":58},"4th century CE",301,400,"lettering","low",[60,64],{"_":61,"type":62,"ref":63},"Megara Hyblaea","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462307",{"_":65,"type":66,"ref":67},"Megara Iblea","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/8063661",[69],[70,71],37.2038,15.18274,[],"Italy","Sicily",{"_":76,"role":77,"ref":78},"Antiquarium di Megara Hyblaia","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/104",{"_":80,"mainLang":81,"languages":82},"Ancient Greek","grc",[80],{"n":84,"url":85,"height":86,"width":87,"desc":88,"surfaceType":89},"screen","ISic004390_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","front",[],[92,93],"À propos d’une inscription funéraire paléochrétienne de Mégara Hyblaea, 2011","Mégara Hyblaea. 7, La ville classique, hellénistique et romaine, 2018",[95,96],"DFXDQ8GT","5UHWUE4K",[98,99,100,14,18,101,102,103,104,105,102,106,107,81],"isic004390","fragmentary early christian funerary inscription",{"_":11},"marble","megara hyblaea","megara iblea","italy","sicily","antiquarium di megara hyblaia","ancient greek","\u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">fragment (physical) a\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"aa-l1-interpret